              levels and consists of 20 questions to be answered in 40 minutes.
              All students may compete in the individual contest; students may
              not compete at more than one level. The 7th grade contest includes
              arithmetic, simple introductory algebra very basic geometry. The
              8th grade individual contest covers these topics along with more
              complex algebra and additional introductory geometry. Each
              correct answer on the individual contest is worth 3 points,
              for a total of 60 points. A team's total for this event is the
              sum of the top four contestants’ scores in each grade.</p>
